tioned CoF for no manna.<br>
<br>
&quot;The existance of manaburn confirms that VI (finally) thinks that we should be able to kill in one shot, provided we can survive long enough to make that shot. I agree. It is a weapon we -deserve- as wizards, it doesn't sound one bit overpowered to me. At least 3 classes have an invulnerability spell to try and negate our burn. Enchanters have unresistable mesmerize &amp; manadrain. Necros can try to beat us to the draw with Lifeburn. Most others have a fighting chance to interrupt us. -Everybody- can run beyond casting range in 6 seconds, if they invest in a horse.&quot;<br>
<br>
Mannaburn isn't stopped by DA type spells it goes right through them. <br>
<br>
Lifeburn will not kill you unless the necro is raid buffed and you aren't (simple math here it will do 2/3 of his hp due to the pvp dmg nerf so unless 2/3 of his hp is = to all your hp you can't die)<br>
<br>
People that claim they can avoid all 6 second nukes like IC by movement are even more silly than those who claim they can't be backstabbed ever in pvp.  <br>
<br>
As far as interupting 1 good yonder, 1 lucky channeling roll, 1 time when you &quot;step into the nuke&quot;, 1 tiny lag spike,  just the smallest bit of luck or skill and they are dead.  This doesn't even take into acount nukes delivered from around corners, inside rocks, and through walls. Nor does it take into acount nukes delivered while flying overhead. Hell what about begining to cast as they run at you from a good distance away. They will be dead long before they reach you or just after.  If your class doesn't have the bash skill then you wont interupt a 6 second spell if they get it half done before you get on them.<br>
<br>
The only class your right about is enchanters.  No enc with rapture should ever let a wizard mannaburn them once they know where you are.  Even in that case its still an unbalanced initial attack.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=setch>Setch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/26/02 1:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ummm....</span><hr size=1> &quot;Mannaburn isn't stopped by DA type spells it goes right through them.&quot;<br>
<br>
This contradicts what I was told by a DA class. I appologize if I am wrong; I thought I had it from an authority.<br>
<br>
In any case regarding mobility, from a dueling perspective, if I had manaburn and started to cast it I would expect my target to be long gone before it went off. I would expect a long range fight from that point forward, with MB serving mainly as a deterrent.<br>
<br>
Of course (as I'm sure you are itching to point out) you aren't looking from a dueling perspective. So naturally you see this ability for its gank potential. I'm seeing it for its ability to turn wizards into a credible threat for targets that -see- us (whereas we were previously listed as &quot;meat&quot; on practically every other class's dueling forum); you're looking at the same skill for its exploitability.<br>
<br>
But I think there are a lot of wizards who see it from my angle; pvp and non alike. We see it as a evener in duels, and we see it as a feature to define our role in group combat; ie if the wizard can take out the enemy's cleric or bard, then maybe the wizard is actually worth having on board.<br>
<br>
Obviously it is exploitable, and as long as it is, people will exploit it. But this does not mean that the damage itself has to be nerfed - just the repercussions. PvP wizards have suggested eliminating loot rights for manaburn kills. I myself have suggested that manaburn could have its damage scaled such that it only does full damage if the wizard is in a full group.<br>
<br>
If you took both of those suggestions together, wizards would retain our newfound group value, without being pigeonholed even further as a ganking class.<br>
<br>
I don't think we sound like money grubbing wizards crying that we won't be able to harvest fungis... personally I won't be able to harvest fungi's regardless of the outcome =)<br>
<br>
I just like it that for the first time since I started reading EQ boards online, wizards are being recognized as formidable adversaries to the powerful, not just the weak and unprepared. It is a status which the wizard class damn well deserves, in my oppinion, and I would say that whether I played one or not. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=booboo>BooBoo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/1/02 3:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ummm....</span><hr size=1> Reguards to Elnerick's Entombment of Ice<br>
<br>
I used to think this spell had no use.  Then I teamed up with a SK friend of mine.  He'd pull, I'd stun then cast this spell.  This spell would land then I would wait a few seconds and finish the mob off with Conflaguration.  This spell kinda worked like a concussion + nuke since he could regain aggro before root broke.  Granted it wasnt super mana efficient and in most cases this spell is used as much as halo of light but I'm still glad to have any spell Verant will give me.<br>
<br>
